Finding and Making Databases
Nutrition and Ingredient Databases
USDA Food Data Central: Maintained by the United States Department of Agriculture, this database offers extensive information on food composition, nutrients, and ingredients. Itâ€™s useful for applications needing detailed food information beyond just identification.
Open Food Facts: A collaborative database containing information on food products from around the world, including ingredients, nutritional content, and barcodes. This could help verify product-specific foods and packaged items.
Edamam Food and Nutrition Database: A commercial database that provides detailed nutrition data, recipes, and ingredient lists, ideal for apps that also need nutritional analysis alongside identification.
